cs.DC, cs.SC, cs.NA, cs.SE, cs.CE 

This paper involves high-performance computing and simulation of complex physical phenomena, which suggests it could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories. 

- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is the most likely category, as the paper focuses on the scalability and performance of the Octo-Tiger code on HPC systems. 
- cs.SC (Scientific Computing and Numerical Analysis) is also a likely category, as the paper describes the simulation of stellar mergers using hydrodynamics and gravity calculations. 
- cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) is another possible category, as the paper discusses the use of finite volume grid-based methods for the simulations. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is a possible category, as the paper describes the use of high-level programming abstractions to manage the complexity of the code and the heterogeneous HPC systems. 
- cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) is also a possible category, as the paper involves the simulation of physical phenomena using computational methods.
